Let $f$ be the cost of one pound of feathers and $g$ be the cost of one ounce of gold. Then, the following two equations are true:
\begin{align*}
8f+2g&=932,\\
14f+3g&=1402.
\end{align*}

full_steps:
Let $f$ be the cost of one pound of feathers and $g$ be the cost of one ounce of gold. Then, the following two equations are true:
\begin{align*}
8f+2g&=932,\\
14f+3g&=1402.
\end{align*}
